r Institutionalisierung in Akademien sowie ihrer Verbreitung durch Drucker bzw. Verlage.  aThe volume contains the proceedings of a conference of the German and Italian Societies for Research into the 18th Century. They range from the Latin-based scholarship of the early 18th century to late-Enlightenment engagement with issues posed by the natural sciences and the theory of culture. The first section "Contacts" is comparative in its approach, dealing with such things as correspondence, change of location, change of context, national standpoints in the evaluation of literature, contrastive scholarly ideals, translations. The second section "Institutions" assembles studies on academicism in opera and drama, the institutionalization of scholarship in academies, and the dissemination of scholarly work by the agency of printers and publishers.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aLearning and scholarshipzGermanyxHistoryy18th centuryvCongresses. 0aLearning and scholarshipzItalyxHistoryy18th centuryvCongresses. 4aDeutschland. 4aGeschichte 1700-1800. 4aItalien. 4aKongress. 4aKulturbeziehungen. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aAGAZZI, ELENA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAREND, ELISABETH, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBEISE, ARND, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBERGER, GÜNTER, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBREMER, THOMAS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCAMPA, CECILIA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCANTARUTTI, GIULIA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCusatelli, Giorgio, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1